<promed@promedmail.org>
[Clinical signs of distemper include dyspnea, ataxia, clonic convulsions,
spasms of the hind legs, ascending paralysis, progressive blindness, loss
of appetite, emaciation, diarrhea and coma. -Mod.PC
[There is a superb discussion of the disease in raccoons in the archived
file Canine distemper, raccoons - USA (Minnesota) (02) 19990803.1330, cited
above. -Man. Ed. DS
